Magnitogorsk Hires Gan to Head Unit Supplying Ford, GM, Renault

-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 
2011-10-07T07:56:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-07/magnitogorsk-hires-gan-to-head-unit-supplying-ford-gm-renault.html
OAO Magnitogorsk Iron & Steel hired
Roman Gan, formerly of Benteler Automotive and OAO Sollers, to
head a unit supplying steel products to carmakers including Ford
Motors Co., General Motors Co., Renault SA and Volkswagen AG.  The Interkos-IV unit in Leningrad region supplies stamped
and prefabricated parts and is expanding capacity from 250,000
units a year now, Magnitogorsk said in a statement today.  “This appointment will enable us to more efficiently meet
the needs of the large cluster of car manufacturers that has
formed in the northwestern region of  Russia ,” Boris Dubrovsky,
Magnitogorsk chief executive officer, said in the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
